.TH PIN "1" "September 2001" "pin" 
.SH NAME
pin \- Package InformatioN 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pin  
[OPTION] [PACKAGENAME/FILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Pin searches the installed packages (rpm -qi, -ql)
and/or the ARCHIVES.gz file for the desired information.
It shows also README, README.SuSE, FAQ, when available.
.PP
It is also possible to search through different version with
the -v option, if you have the ARCHIVES.gz from it.
You have to copy ARCHIVES.gz to /usr/share/pin/ for this option,
don`t forget to name it, e.g. 7.1-ppc, 7.2-i386.
.TP
pin
open a dialog box and wait for searchstring
.TP
pin name
searches for a package <name>
.TP
pin -f name 
greping also if package was found
.TP
pin -v name    
searches through another version, not the default
